CALL FOR REGISTRATION

The next

         International Category Theory Conference

will take place in Genoa (Italy), from Sunday, 20 June, through
Saturday, 26 June, 2010.

Registration is now open at the website

http://ct2010.disi.unige.it/

where a list of hotels is already available as well as all the
information about the conference. Please consider that the region
around Genoa attracts many tourists in summer, so it is advisable to
book a hotel as soon as you can.

Contributions in all aspects of Category Theory are welcome and we
especially encourage experts to submit work on its applications as
well as on its foundations. If you would like to give a talk, please
submit a title and a one-page abstract by email to
Robert Rosebrugh <rrosebrugh@mta.ca>
before 10 May.

All talks will be held at DIMA-DISI, via Dodecaneso 35, Genova.

Looking forward to seeing you in Genoa!
Pino Rosolini
for the CT2010 Committees



[For admin and other information see: http://www.mta.ca/~cat-dist/ ]

